    description:
      "About Paperspace\n\nPaperspace is a cloud computing company creating simple and scalable accelerated computing applications. Our goal is to allow individuals and professional teams to build applications with ease -\u00c2\u00a0 from Machine Learning to 3D graphics.\n\nPaperspace is backed by leading investors including Y Combinator, Initialized Capital, Battery Ventures, and Intel Capital.\n\nOur Team\u00c2\u00a0\n\nPaperspace values technical excellence in an open and inclusive environment. The team is primarily based in NYC, but we have a strong remote/hybrid team. Communication is paramount and mutual respect is at the core of our collaborative work environment.\u00c2\u00a0We are also committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. We believe creating a more diverse team directly impacts our ability to collaborate effectively, build a better community, and produce better products.\n\nThe Role\n\nGradient is our end-to-end MLOps platform that allows users to explore their data, train their models, and deploy them. Notebook IDE, Workflows, and Deployments make up the products we offer to users in addition to platform entitles such as storage providers, datasets, secrets, models, and metrics. We\u00e2\u0080\u0099re building a complete end-to-end platform so users can have a delightful experience at every step of the way to lower the barrier to machine learning and make it more accessible to all.\n\nAs Head of Product, you\u00e2\u0080\u0099ll bring your domain expertise and experience managing technical products to set direction and own success for an exciting problem space. You will partner across engineering, design, marketing, and sales to shape and execute the product strategy. In addition, you work with users and metrics to identify new opportunities to improve the product and help define the roadmap.\n\nWhat we're looking for\n\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 6+ years of experience managing a technical product and working with multiple product teams\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Entrepreneurial spirit, ideally have started your own companies or have worked in a fast-paced environment working with ambiguity and focusing on driving impact\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Experience writing comprehensive user stories that motivate and guide engineering efforts with the right amount of constraints\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Demonstrated design and UX sensibilities\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Ability to communicate the product value and opportunities across a wide range of audiences from engineering, marketing, and sales to individual users and B2B customers\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Experience shipping high-quality products from planning to launch to maintenance\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Ability to make trade-offs effectively in regards to both engineering and product requirements, while also effectively balancing short term and long term needs\n\nWhat you'll be doing\n\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Working with cross-functional teams to own the end to end journey for users\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Deeply immerse yourself in the industry and the user\u00e2\u0080\u0099s world to understand patterns and to maintain a strong mental model of the market\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Evangelize the product opportunities to provide clarity and inspiration to all teams\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Maintain a product backlog and roadmap to communicate business goals and timelines to ensure alignment across the board\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Grow a team of product managers and facilitate a culture so that they can do their best work\n\nWho you\u00e2\u0080\u0099ll be working with\n\nDillon Erb - CEO and Co-Founder\nDillon describes himself as collaborative and accessible but is also a technical person who prefers results-oriented strategies. The CEO is looking for a self-starter who isn\u00e2\u0080\u0099t afraid to dive into the details and is very process-driven.\n\nBenefits\n\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Multiple health care insurance options with premium plans in addition to vision and dental insurance plans\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 401(k) Plan with employer matching\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Commuter benefits with a contribution from the company \n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Responsible Time Off Policy \n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Generous and flexible parental leave\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Fitness & wellness benefit\n\u00e2\u0080\u00a2 Remote friendly and hybrid office environment for New York team members\n\nWe are an equal opportunity employer that values and welcomes diversity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status.\n\n#LI-Remote",
